name: Usama Bin Murad
review_text: This time it was an afternoon wedding venue. Great weather to be outdoor. Bright sunlight. Breeze. Not too cold. So great weather for sitting out in the garden experience! The setting is nice for a wedding ceremony. The stage is set. The tables all laid out with ample space to move around. Food was really good. The rice looked fresh and delicious. The seekh kebab really moist and a great taste. The Gaajar ka Halwa needed more cooking time! And the Shahi Tukray cannot be made from custard! Napkins need to be clean! Suggestion to make a clear separate passage for the event areas. Not a good experience coming through the path where there are people coming in and out of a restaurant like space. Also one has to pass by the cooking area. Not a good feel as one is in the wedding ceremony mode.

name: Rizwan Sohail
review_text: Went there couple of times, always a good visit. Went for first time maybe 10 years ago. Good lawns, especially if the season is good, its better to sit outside. Its away from main city and the only restaurant in the vicinity therefore quite a good place to have a nice evening. Serving all kinds of food from desi-pakistani dishes to continental. In dessert we really like their jaleebi and gulab jamun. Especially in these covid times its better, as they have outdoor seating. Easy to reach both from islambad and rawalpindi. Its located near to the highway on a scenic road. Best is to combine it with some other visit in the vicinty like the musuem of natural history or lok virsa. Pakistan monument is also nearby, 5 mins drive from the place. Classic place to have a quite dinner. During summers evenings are the best time to go as its abit cooler in the area. From the main highway drive is around 5 mins after the turn. Its also convenient to plan gatherings of office and friends. Being in quite area you escape the city life for sometime. Jungle all around the resturant adds to its beauty. Overall a good experience, hoping to visit another time soon.

name: Khalid Yazdani Shah
review_text: Set in the idyllic green area very close to the Lok Virsa museum this old home converted into a restaurant is a must visit place in Islamabad. No it was not started in 1969 nor is the building in which its indoor dining area is situated was built in 1969 (it's much older) the name was just chosen randomly. The food quality is excellent and there is a decent range of items on the menu. The outdoor seating area is much more popular even before COVID times and it's an awesome place to enjoy a breakfast or lunch on a sunny winter day or dinner in summers. Even if you do not have a sweet tooth do try their out of this world crispy Jaleebi Ø¬Ù„ÛŒØ¨ÛŒ and you will not be disappointed. Highly recommended especially nowadays in the winter during the daytime!
